  "notes": "Claude Sonnet 4.6 run under same conditions as Kimi-128k. Per-task scores are numerically identical to Kimi-128k across all 10 tasks (same breakdown, same total). This is not a bug — it reflects the deterministic seeded environment + deterministic judge: two capable models that solve the task correctly produce identical outcomes, so they receive identical scores. The residual 2.5-pt-per-task gap below 100 is a judge sub-criterion ceiling (Robustness capped at 12/15 on T4/T5, Observability capped at ~8.67/10). Finding: ComtradeBench currently has strong *binary* discriminative power (frontier vs sub-frontier: Kimi/Claude 97.5 vs Llama 89.3) but NOT fine-grained discriminative power *among* frontier models. A harder T9 variant with steeper mid-episode escalation would push the ceiling down (see Limitations)."
